Then the issue is probably MacLib’s resolveIcon() bug.

It checks:

name:find("rbxassetid://")
but if you pass a raw number string, it converts to:

rbxassetid://122532961577506
So that part is okay.

But your direct test should be:

img.Image = "rbxassetid://122532961577506"
not raw:

img.Image = "122532961577506"
Since 18824089198 works and 122532961577506 doesn’t, even as texture ID, then Roblox is refusing to render that specific image.

Fix: re-upload it and use the new image ID.

Or use the non-Roblox route:

writefile("pork.png", game:HttpGet("IMAGE_URL_HERE"))

local PigFace = getcustomasset("pork.png")
-- or getsynasset("pork.png")

Image = PigFace,
WatermarkImage = PigFace,
SidebarWatermarkImage = PigFace,
That bypasses Roblox asset loading completely.



